Yes, I can help you fix that issue. To address this, you can use a tolerance value when checking if the current time is equal to one of the pause times. For example, you could use a tolerance of 0.1 seconds, and check if the current time is within 0.1 seconds of a pause time, instead of checking for exact equality. Here's the updated code:


```javascript
var vid = document.getElementById("myVideo");
